Content:
Alan Lipscombe Traffic & Transportation Consultants is a company based in the Republic of Ireland. Having been established since the end of 2007, this specialised independent consultancy has successfully completed a number of commissions for Clients in the private, semi-state and public sectors. Projects range from transport modelling /forecasting and the preparation of economic assessments for strategic highway schemes, to the preparation of travel plans aimed at providing alternative modes of travel to the private car. Between 1997 and 2007 Alan Lipscombe was employed by Colin Buchanan and Partners (CBP see Colin Buchanan (town planner)) as the manager of their Galway Office, having moved there as the senior transportation engineer for the Galway Land Use and Transportation Study. After the completion of that study in 1999 Alan worked for CBP throughout the West of Ireland on a range of projects: including N6 Galway City Outer Bypass,[1] Limerick Southern Ring Road and Limerick Tunnel,[2] Limerick Planning Land Use and Transportation Study, the NUI Galway New Engineering Building and Mobility Management Plan, Ennis Traffic Model and various travel plans and development related projects. Before moving to Ireland Alan was involved in a wide variety of transport-related studies for CBP throughout the UK, Malta and Indonesia. Alan Lipscombe Traffic and Transportion Consultancy was established on October 1, 2007 by Alan Lipscombe. Based on the West Coast of Ireland, the company has established connections throughout the world.
